cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with constructive mathematics and explores different encodings of Noetherian sets. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper is written in the dependently typed programming language Agda. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possibility as the paper mentions decidable equality and explores the properties and connections of different encodings. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as Noetherian sets are related to finiteness and the paper explores the relation between Noetherianness and other notions of finiteness. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with programming language concepts and their properties.
